In Kotlin, enum classes require a default constructor for each enum constant. However, if you want to create an enum class with no default constructor for the enum constants, you can define properties and functions in the enum class itself rather than as part of the constructor.

Here's an example:

```kotlin
enum class Weekday {
    MONDAY {
        override fun getDayName(): String {
            return "Monday"
        }

        override fun isWeekend(): Boolean {
            return false
        }
    },
